<span id="freeTextContainer1478297155483140058">This story was so well-written I had to check the front cover a couple of times that it was indeed &quot;A Novel&quot;! The story switches back and forth in time, and the author does it so well I was easily able to read without the dissonance I often feel with the technique. The story of a white Muslim woman in Ethiopia during the times of great changes, this story is also a scrabble-lover&apos;s dream. Words like QAT, SUQ, MIRQANA, and more are used throughout. I won&apos;t have any trouble remembering those words</span>
