  <span id="freeText4057492311318326861" style="display:none">An interesting book set in Ethiopia and London. A sensitive and thoughtful account of devastation of dictatorship, revolution and destruction in Ethiopia and the struggles of being a refugee in London - the sense of displacement and loss, whilst dealing with the past traumas of war. Also an interesting analysis of differences in practices of Islam, depending on different cultures and traditions. I am unfamiliar with what the political scene was in Ethiopia in '70's but sense that her political analysis had a Western perspective. But certainly a book worth reading. </span>
